-- Japan Seeks to Triple Emission Offset Partners, Kyodo Reports
-- B y   C h i s a k i   W a t a n a b e
-- 2013-11-07T02:34:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-11-07/japan-seeks-to-triple-emission-offset-partners-kyodo-reports.html
Japan  plans to triple the number of
countries with which it has bilateral environmental technology
transfer arrangements to offset the country’s carbon dioxide
emissions, Kyodo News agency reported today.  The country plans to hold an international conference in
Tokyo in October to discuss developing technology for the
environment, Kyodo said, citing a summary of Japan’s climate
change diplomacy strategy to be announced at United Nations
climate talks which will open Nov. 11 in  Poland .  Japan seeks to set a 5-year target of about 11 trillion yen
($112 billion) in investment in research and development for
environmental and energy technology from public and private
sectors, according to the report.  Eight countries including Indonesia and Mongolia have
signed up for the bilateral program,  according  to the Japanese
government.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Chisaki Watanabe in  Tokyo  at 
